claim.claim-text:
12. A method of stabilizing a tree using the stabilizing assembly of claim 1, comprising the following steps: 
placing the planted tree in a perpendicular orientation with the ground; 
inserting at least two stakes into the ground alongside of, and parallel to the tree, on opposing sides of the tree in an approximately straight-line orientation having the tree being stabilized at the approximate midpoint; 
holding the folded end of the woven rectangle, passing a fastener material through the reinforcing member at the folded end and affixing the fastener material to the first stake; 
bringing the two open ends of the woven rectangle around the tree in an orientation parallel to the ground; 
bringing the reinforcing members at each of the open ends of the assembly into close proximity and inserting through each a second strand of fastening material, thereby closing or effectively closing the assembly around the tree; 
extending and affixing the unattached end of the second strand of fastening material to the second stake and tightening the assembly to stabilize the tree.

